## Task 3: Fix and Maintain Category Taxonomy

### Current Problem
Categories inconsistent across blog posts, not properly maintained, causing navigation and organization issues.

### 3.1 Audit Current Categories

**Scan all blog posts** in `src/content/blogs/*.md`

**Extract unique categories**:
```javascript
// Script to audit
const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const matter = require('gray-matter');

const blogsDir = path.join(__dirname, '../src/content/blogs');
const files = fs.readdirSync(blogsDir).filter(f => f.endsWith('.md'));

const categories = new Map();

files.forEach(file => {
  const content = fs.readFileSync(path.join(blogsDir, file), 'utf8');
  const { data } = matter(content);
  
  if (data.category) {
    const count = categories.get(data.category) || 0;
    categories.set(data.category, count + 1);
  }
});

console.log('\nCurrent Categories:');
categories.forEach((count, cat) => {
  console.log(`- ${cat}: ${count} posts`);
});
```

